Narrator

I sat down in my office chair and sighed deeply.

Narrator

I sat down in my office chair and sighed deeply.

Player

"Sorry you didn't get to be Vice President for longer."

Player

"Well, we had a good run."

Albin Clavin

"It's an honor just to have been chosen."

Albin Clavin

"I can't tell if you're being sarcastic."

Narrator

Gloria's arms were crossed. She barely looked at me.

Player

"I guess all that change you hoped for will have to wait."

Albin Clavin

"Thanks for that."

Narrator

Gloria gave me an uncomfortable-looking smile.

Narrator

As the director gave the signal to roll the camera, I fumbled with the notes I had prepared.

Player

"People of Sordland, let me be honest with you."

Player

"The truth is, I'm just plain tired."

Player

"The truth is, I failed you."

Player

"Soll and Alphonso left the country in shambles. There was nothing I could've done to make things better."

Player

"My political opponents blocked me at every turn. By trying to compromise with them, I compromised your trust."

Player

"Constant distraction from our enemies abroad made it impossible for me to focus on improving the situation at home."

Player

"Sordland is too complicated a country for a single President to make a difference. I will resign at the end of my term."

Player

"At the end of my term, I will be ending my political career to spend more time with my family."

Player

"At the end of my term, I will be ending my political career to take some time for myself."

Player

"At the end of my term, I will be ending my political career for personal reasons."

Player

"People of Sordland, it gives me great pleasure and great sorrow to address you for what may be the last time."

Player

"As for who should be running the country in my stead..."

Player

"I urge you to vote for Lileas Graf."

Player

"It has been an honor to serve you."

Narrator

Petr came in without knocking.

Narrator

I was completely on my own now, not beholden to friends, colleagues or family members. I could go wherever and do whatever I wanted.

Monica

"What's the plan, Mr. President?"

Monica

"Although I also wouldn't mind joining Franc in United Contana."

Player

"Let's stay in Sordland."

Monica

"Or we could spend some time in Arcasia to learn from their women's rights movement -- don't you still have shares in that electronics business over there?"

Player

"Let's give Arcasia a try. We can always come back to Sordland if we hate it."

Player

"You know what? I think United Contana is the place for us."

Monica

"Franc's certainly given it a ringing endorsement."

Monica

"Maybe you two could finally mend your relationship."

Monica

"Maybe you two could finally mend your relationship."

Monica

"If Franc's to be believed, we'll never want to go back."

Narrator

Monica smiled and gave me a big hug.

Monica

"...and with our budget, the sky's the limit."

Player

"We could get a mansion on the Benfi coast."

Player

"I've always wanted to take a more active role in Underhall Construction."

Monica

"It'd give us a chance to redeem ourselves after that scene at the festival."

Monica

"With the size of your stake in the team, they'd have to let you do whatever you want."

Monica

"I've been meaning to spend more time over there."

Monica

"Really? Well, at least staying in Holsord wouldn't be too disruptive for Deana..."

Monica

"That's true. And it would be easy for both of us to stay involved in politics, if we wanted to."

Monica

"Let's break the news to Deana tomorrow."

Narrator

As my closest friend, I'd asked him to help me decide on a retirement plan.

Player

"I'd like to think about my other options before deciding on anything."

Petr Vectern

"Well, obviously, if I were you, I'd go to the Benfi coast."

Player

"I'd like to think about my other options before deciding on anything."

Petr Vectern

"Have you thought about joining Franc abroad? The two Rayne men, conquering the continent."

Petr Vectern

"Have you thought about moving abroad? There's that electronics corporation you invested in in Arcasia -- Armadillo or something?"

Petr Vectern

"There's always Anrica -- I know you think you could do a better job with the football team than the current manager."

Petr Vectern

"A house on the coast in Benfi would be my next choice if I were you. A retirement cliche, but for a reason..."

Petr Vectern

"Come on, Anton, what'll it be?"

Player

"I'm staying in Holsord."

Petr Vectern

"All right! Arcasia, then."

Player

"Sure."

Player

"Actually, I intend to keep a low profile."

Player

"I suppose so."

Petr Vectern

"Yes! I knew you were going to say that!"

Narrator

As I finished my drink, I wondered what life after the presidency would look like...

Petr Vectern

"Yes! You won't regret it, Anton."

Player

"I can't wait."

Player

"It's settled, then. Benfi it is. I hope you like shellfish."

Player

"It's settled, then. Rayne Wines it is."

Player

"I'd rather go to Benfi."

Player

"I can't wait."

Player_Italic

I pulled Monica in for a kiss.

Narrator

My first thought was of my vineyard in Erlory.

Narrator

A villa on a sunny hillside and a career in winemaking didn't sound bad at all.

Narrator

I could also stay in Holsord. It wouldn't be very exciting, but I'd have the chance to see my daughter.

Narrator

I could also stay in Holsord and get more involved in Underhall Construction. It wouldn't be glamorous, but I could get rich.

Narrator

We'd finally have the time we needed to mend our broken relationship.

Narrator

But then again...

Narrator

On the other hand...

Narrator

There was always Anrica. I knew I could do a better job with the team than the current manager.

Narrator

I could go to the Benfi coast.

Narrator

With my budget, I could afford a little house on the beach.

Narrator

I could move abroad. I still owned stakes in Armadine, the electronics company in Arcasia. The board would welcome me with open arms.

Narrator

Franc was in United Contana, but Armadine, the electronics company I owned shares in, was in Arcasia. I could pivot to a career in business.

Narrator

I carefully weighed the pros and cons.

Player_Italic

I decided to move to Arcasia.

Player_Italic

I thought to myself that I could always just remain in Holsord. I already had lots of connections. Yeah. That was a good idea.

Player_Italic

I thought to myself that I could always just retire on the Benfi coast. I do need some resting time anyways. Yeah. That was a good idea.

Narrator

I was headed for a new beginning in a new country.

Narrator

I was headed for a new career and a new beginning.

Narrator

I was headed for a new home and a new beginning.

Narrator

I paced the floor of my office in the Maroon Palace. The camera crew was due to arrive any moment now.

Player

"I stand by my support of Lileas Graf and the USP."

Player

"I stand by my support of the PFJP."

Player

"I stand by my support of the NFP."

Player

"I stand by my support of the WPB and CSP."

Player

"I must thank my wife, Monica, the First Lady of Sordland, for being such a strong woman."

Player

"I am grateful to walk this path in life with the amazing Monica Rayne, who has supported me through the last four years."

Player

"We have successfully finished the de-Sollinisation of Sordland. A new era has begun!"

Player

"Today, Tarquin Soll's cult of personality is no more. His images have been erased from public places."

Player

"Tarquin Soll was finally brought to justice as was due."

Player

"I must thank Monica for her hard work in leading the campaign to expand the rights of Sordish women."

Player

"We made the once-untouchable Soll answer for his crimes!"

Player

"When I look back, I see achievements that will never be forgotten."

Player

"I thank my family for making me the man I am today. I am very lucky to have them."

Player

"As I promised four years ago, I made law enforcement the focus of my administration, and our country is safer and more secure for it."

Player

"I took responsibility to strengthen our law enforcement and I delivered the best possible results in four years' time."

Player

"As I promised four years ago, I made military the focus of my administration and greatly strengthened our defense forces."

Player

"I took responsibility for strengthening our military and delivered the best possible results in four years' time."

Player

"As I promised four years ago, I made education the focus of my administration and greatly expanded our services to the Sordish people."

Player

"When you asked me to fix our education system, I took responsibility and delivered the best results in four years' time."

Player

"When you asked me to fix our healthcare system, I took responsibility and delivered the best results in four years' time."

Player

"And most importantly, I thank *you* for supporting me through these difficult years."

Player

"And my greatest thanks goes out to all of you who came here today. You are the backbone of this campaign. Your noise is shaking the whole country!"

Player

"I must also thank every one of our citizens who resisted and fought with us."

Narrator

I had to pause and had a few sips of water before continuing.

Player

"Unfortunately, most of my term saw a period of emergency. But I had to take action, and it proved to be justified."

Player

"We completed one of the biggest infrastructure projects in Sordland's history, which led to rapid economic development."

Player

"Since 1954, Sords have been given cliffs to climb, and found the tenacity to climb them. Now, we can see the valley below."

Player

"You once protested our corrupt political establishment and you elected me to fight for you. To finally put Sordland first."

Player

"With the power you entrusted upon us, my administration fought to serve your interests alone."

Player

"Our government showed this nation steady, consistent and principled leadership with a clear and positive plan."

Player

"They did not believe in me when I first proposed our constitutional changes. I proved everyone wrong."

Player

"Economic instability and depression plagued our country, but together, we overcame them."

Player

"We managed to fix the recession and put it behind us. Now we can safely begin building our country back up again."

Player

"We were faced with existential threats from both inside and outside. But we eliminated all who threatened the integrity of our great nation."

Player

"Plagued by political turmoil in our first days in office, I took decisive action and brought stability to Sordland."

Player

"We improved rural treatment substantially by hiring health staff and upgrading equipment."

Player

"We agreed to pay doctors, nurses and other health staff salaries commensurate with their value to our society."

Player

"We built new hospitals where they were needed. Access to health became available for all."

Player

"Every one of my decisions was made to serve all Sordish citizens regardless of their ethnic background, religion or personal wealth."

Player

"We took steps to protect our proud mother tongue and unified our education in the Sordish language."

Player

"Thanks to our policies, Sordish people can now enjoy more accessible and higher-quality healthcare."

Narrator

I took a look at my supporters.

Player

"Today, Sordish citizens enjoy more services and liberties than ever before."

Player

"Today, every Sordish citizen is entitled to medicine for free!"

Player

"Today, Sordish citizens enjoy a lower retirement age. By five years, no less..."

Player

"Sordland will stand with the CSP against Arcasian capitalism. With the power of the East, Sordland will be the dominant force in Eastern Merkopa."

Player

"As a new member of the CSP, we will be walking towards the future with more confident steps, together with our allies."

Player

"We integrated Sordland into the international arena. Now, Sordland is a member of the CSP."

Player

"We integrated Sordland into the international arena. Now, Sordland is a member of the ATO."

Player

"As a new member of the ATO, we will be walking towards the future with more confident steps, together with our allies."

Player

"Sordland will stand with the ATO against Malenyevism. With the power of the West, Sordland will be the dominant force in Eastern Merkopa."

Player

"We established a minimum wage and expanded rights and legal protection for our workers."

Player

"We built new rural schools and increased access to education."

Player

"We increased the salaries of teachers, principals and other education staff all around the country."

Player

"We improved rural education by purchasing new materials and upgrading old school equipment."

Player

"We provided the Sordish people with higher-quality and more accessible education."

Player

"During our term, the traditional values of Sordland were protected and strengthened like never before."

Player

"As one of my last actions in office, I also made peace with our historical rival, Rumburg, managing the unthinkable."

Player

"We taxed the elites of Sordland to balance the unequal share of wealth across our nation."

Player

"We helped thousands of Sordish citizens with disabilities."

Player

"We helped millions of children and parents with our child benefit policy."

Player

"We enacted policies that protect the interests of the Sordish people."

Player

"We unified our religious system and stopped militant groups from using religion to justify their violence."

Player

"That was not all. I stood at the precipice of a possible war with Rumburg. And rather than giving in to bloodshed, I began a peace process."

Player

"I defended Sordland's international interests and fought for peace in Eastern Merkopa."

Player

"During my term, the minorities of Sordland saw a great expansion of their political and social freedoms like they have never seen before."

Narrator

The crowd was cheering: "President Rayne!"

Player

"I gave the Bludish minority what they wanted for decades. An autonomous Bergia!"

Player

"I worked hard to expand the rights of our minorities. I formed a commission for Bludish rights and gave amnesty to all Bluds prosecuted for their ethnicity."

Player

"We brought free public transportation to all Sordish citizens!"

Player

"I stood in the way of the ultranationalists and I crushed every bill that sought to undermine the Bludish people."

Player

"With increased control over the Central Bank, Sordland will be much swifter in taking action against economic turmoil."

Player

"We now give housing assistance to all Sordish citizens who need it. We're one step closer to eliminating homelessness!"

Player

"Today, every unemployed Sordish citizen is entitled to government assistance until they find a job."

Player

"I have always had the best interests of our people at heart, and I will continue to do so."

Player

"One of our historic achievements was to pay off all student debts. We erased it completely."

Player

"In the face of foreign intervention and internal militants, we enacted new security laws and eliminated the threats."

Player

"By establishing the Free Trade Commission, we ensured healthy competition, so that our citizens can buy higher-quality products for less."

Player

"I worked long and hard to ensure a brighter future for our country and our people."

Player

"My term saw a great expansion of women's rights. Sordish women now finally have a voice."

Player

"In the last four years, the women of this country won a decades-long fight against the patriarchy."

Player

"I de-segregated our education system which had deep roots in misogyny. Now every Sordish student is equal."

Player

"I heard the pleas of our women and acted to represent their rights. I enacted laws that protect and liberate the women of this great nation."

Player

"The truth is, I have done my part for this country. And I am proud of what I achieved."

Player

"The truth is, it is important to let go and allow new leadership to take the reigns."

Player

"My dear citizens, this has been the greatest honor bestowed upon me as a fellow countryman."

Player

"At the end of my term, I will be ending my political career for personal reasons."

Player

"I have demonstrated that Sordland can improve as a society. Never lose hope, my fellow citizens."

Player

"I gave my heart and soul to serve this beautiful nation."

Player

"Our people are great and unique. We are destined for great things."

Player

"I wish my successor the best of luck. For this is the greatest test of oneself."

Player

"Sordland must walk the path of malenyevism to achieve true parity in society."

Player

"Our nation should adopt the middle-ground solution of Valgslandian socialism to advance."

Player

"This country can combine strong elements of socialism and democracy to provide an alternative."

Player

"I'd like to make a statement regarding the future of the country."

Player

"I'd like to conclude on that note."

Player

"The Colonel has provided a different and stronger path for the future of Sordland. One we should follow."

Player

"Our society, culture and the values Sords represent must be at the forefront of any governance."

Player

"Our country is great as is and there is little reason to make a drastic change to steer from this course."

Player

"Sordland can enrich itself and be part of a new world order with an incentive-driven capitalist structure."

Player

"Our nation must unlock the ambitions and potentials of individuals with material rewards to compete with the world."

Player

"It is possible to find balance in the system of the west and still achieve high living standards for many."

Player

"Sordland should be a beacon of liberty and democracy. We can cherish our idealistic values."

Player

"Our country should provide all types of freedoms and allow for safe transition of power regardless of who the people choose."

Player

"Whichever way Sordland may evolve to, democracy must take a part in the form of government."

Player

"We wrote history when we celebrated our changes to the outdated Constitution of 1929."

Player

"We have amended our once-untouchable constitution and opened the way for further reforms."
